sed with a wide range of versions of SPSS Statistics. However, you can also=
 run the Wilcoxon signed-rank test using the <strong>Nonparametric Tests &g=
t; Related Samples</strong> procedure in SPSS Statistics, which is availabl=
e for <strong>versions 18 to 30</strong> and the <strong>subscription versi=
on</strong> of SPSS Statistics. This <strong>Nonparametric Tests &gt; Relat=
ed Samples</strong> procedure provides <strong>additional statistics</stron=
g> and <strong>more graphical options</strong> than the <strong>Legacy Dial=
ogs &gt; 2 Related Samples</strong> procedure. Therefore, we show you how t=
o run the <strong>Nonparametric Tests &gt; Related Samples</strong> procedu=
re and interpret and report the output from it in our enhanced Wilcoxon sig=
ned-rank test guide. You can access the enhanced Wilcoxon signed-rank test =
guide by <a href=3D"https://statistics.laerd.com/pricing.php">subscribing t=
o Laerd Statistics</a>.</p>
=09
