> of SPSS Statistics, with <strong>version 30</strong> and the <strong>subs=
cription version</strong> being the <strong>latest versions</strong> of SPS=
S Statistics. However, in <strong>version 27</strong> and the <strong>subsc=
ription version</strong>, SPSS Statistics introduced a new look to their in=
terface called "<strong>SPSS Light</strong>", replacing the previous look f=
or <strong>versions 26</strong> and <strong>earlier versions</strong>, whic=
